1
00:00:00,970 --> 00:00:03,710
(Episode 59)

2
00:00:15,220 --> 00:00:16,290
(B3 Parking Lot)

3
00:00:24,430 --> 00:00:26,700
Trying to find the evidence
Seo Rin has hidden...

4
00:00:27,000 --> 00:00:28,730
is going to take way too long.

5
00:00:29,600 --> 00:00:33,370
For now, I'll use this video
to tell Grandfather everything.

6
00:00:36,110 --> 00:00:38,380
I hear you're going to be featured
in a news magazine soon?

7
00:00:39,010 --> 00:00:40,010
Yes, I am.

8
00:00:40,650 --> 00:00:44,780
It's such an honor.
It feels like my hard work has paid off.

9
00:00:45,780 --> 00:00:49,650
And it's all thanks to you
for recognizing my potential, Father.

10
00:00:52,720 --> 00:00:56,430
Ever since I came to you
with Dong Seok's child 30 years ago,

11
00:00:56,730 --> 00:00:58,860
and entered this family,
to this very day...

12
00:01:00,030 --> 00:01:04,170
I've put my heart and soul
into Dream Hotel.

13
00:01:06,200 --> 00:01:07,940
That Dong Seok...

14
00:01:09,410 --> 00:01:12,180
By the way, Hwa Young, that...

15
00:01:13,010 --> 00:01:14,910
What was that woman's name again?

16
00:01:15,480 --> 00:01:17,280
The one Dong Seok was so fond of.

17
00:01:19,220 --> 00:01:20,590
Jung Suk Hee?

18
00:01:21,290 --> 00:01:24,090
You're talking about Jung Suk Hee, right?

19
00:01:24,690 --> 00:01:27,790
I'm going to tell Grandfather everything.

20
00:01:30,930 --> 00:01:33,100
You still remember her name?

21
00:01:35,270 --> 00:01:37,540
How could I possibly forget her name?

22
00:01:38,670 --> 00:01:41,340
The name of the woman
the man I loved preferred.

23
00:01:42,010 --> 00:01:45,280
I'll never forget it,
not in 30 years, not even in 50.

24
00:01:46,480 --> 00:01:48,950
Don't be ridiculous. She was an orphan,

25
00:01:49,010 --> 00:01:53,080
a girl with no family background.
I couldn't let her into our family.

26
00:01:53,550 --> 00:01:57,660
We couldn't accept her as a match for
Dong Seok, heir to Dream Group, could we?

27
00:01:58,260 --> 00:02:00,330
So Grandfather disapproved of my mom?

28
00:02:01,330 --> 00:02:04,430
So is that why Mom left Dad...

29
00:02:04,860 --> 00:02:06,460
and had us in secret?

30
00:02:07,300 --> 00:02:12,240
I only accepted Seo Rin
as my granddaughter because of you.

31
00:02:12,670 --> 00:02:16,110
It's because you're so good
with the business.

32
00:02:16,810 --> 00:02:19,380
Even if Jung Suk Hee had shown up
with a son,

33
00:02:19,710 --> 00:02:24,150
I would never have accepted him.
Not a chance. Absolutely not.

34
00:02:25,120 --> 00:02:26,120
What?

35
00:02:26,820 --> 00:02:30,390
So is he saying
even if Chae Hwa Young stole us twins,

36
00:02:31,060 --> 00:02:33,020
he would just forgive her...

37
00:02:33,660 --> 00:02:35,590
and turn his back on my mother for good?

38
00:02:40,400 --> 00:02:41,430
Grandfather...

39
00:02:42,200 --> 00:02:45,200
I guess the company means more to him
than anything.

40
00:02:45,970 --> 00:02:49,310
It might not matter to you if we're twins,
but it's a huge deal for me.

41
00:02:49,770 --> 00:02:52,810
I have a lot more at stake than you do.

42
00:02:54,510 --> 00:02:56,350
Seo Rin knew everything all along.

43
00:02:57,750 --> 00:02:58,780
What do I do?

44
00:02:59,350 --> 00:03:01,850
Even if I tell Grandfather
that we're twins,

45
00:03:02,350 --> 00:03:03,420
it's not going to do any good.

46
00:03:15,330 --> 00:03:16,670
My poor mom.

47
00:03:17,270 --> 00:03:18,270
What am I going to do?

48
00:03:19,100 --> 00:03:21,210
Grandfather never even wanted her.

49
00:03:25,010 --> 00:03:26,440
I can't let it end like this.

50
00:03:27,380 --> 00:03:29,410
I will never forgive you, Chae Hwa Young.

51
00:03:30,520 --> 00:03:31,520
Father.

52
00:03:32,020 --> 00:03:35,490
They named me one of the most admired
female CEOs.

53
00:03:37,260 --> 00:03:38,260
Really?

54
00:03:39,860 --> 00:03:42,360
Then I guess a celebration is in order
for Chae Hwa Young.

55
00:03:47,070 --> 00:03:48,070
I'm home.

56
00:03:48,470 --> 00:03:50,940
You're back. Have you eaten yet?

57
00:03:51,270 --> 00:03:52,870
- I did.
- Come sit with us.

58
00:03:54,570 --> 00:03:58,140
Let me just enjoy this.
All the men of my house together.

59
00:03:58,380 --> 00:04:01,310
Gosh, what's so great about looking
at a bunch of boring guys?

60
00:04:01,380 --> 00:04:05,250
I want to feast my eyes
on all my handsome men.

61
00:04:05,350 --> 00:04:07,690
Should have had a daughter then.
No regrets?

62
00:04:07,750 --> 00:04:11,920
You marry off a daughter,
but you gain a daughter-in-law with a son.

63
00:04:12,020 --> 00:04:15,260
I'm going to get daughters-in-law
and treat them like my own daughters.

64
00:04:15,360 --> 00:04:19,430
So basically, you're saying
you'll never let me and my brother go.

65
00:04:20,160 --> 00:04:23,000
- Oh my, that's creepy.
- Don't be fresh.

66
00:04:23,400 --> 00:04:28,170
Mark my words.
I'll have a daughter-in-law on each arm,

67
00:04:28,240 --> 00:04:32,810
we'll go shopping and complain
and talk trash about you two.

68
00:04:32,880 --> 00:04:35,710
I'm going to be a chic and fabulous
mother-in-law.

69
00:04:35,950 --> 00:04:38,780
- Whatever you say.
- I'm going to go wash up.

70
00:04:45,590 --> 00:04:46,590
Lawyer Han.

71
00:04:47,430 --> 00:04:48,930
I'd like to talk about Jun Ho.

72
00:04:54,900 --> 00:04:57,440
My Jun Ho? Is something wrong?

73
00:04:58,540 --> 00:05:00,540
I'm considering him as a son-in-law.

74
00:05:01,240 --> 00:05:03,470
What are your thoughts on the matter,
Lawyer Han?

75
00:05:03,740 --> 00:05:04,740
Excuse me?

76
00:05:05,240 --> 00:05:06,380
What do you mean, son-in-law?

77
00:05:08,050 --> 00:05:11,950
Hold on, are you suggesting that
your daughter marry my son, Jun Ho?

78
00:05:12,180 --> 00:05:15,650
Yes. I think they would make
a perfect match.

79
00:05:18,220 --> 00:05:19,220
I suppose so,

80
00:05:21,190 --> 00:05:24,660
but this is all so sudden.
I'm a little overwhelmed.

81
00:05:25,260 --> 00:05:28,200
On our end, we view a match
between my daughter Seo Rin and Jun Ho...

82
00:05:28,470 --> 00:05:30,230
very favorably.

83
00:05:31,600 --> 00:05:36,370
If she's the woman Jun Ho wants,
we won't stand in the way.

84
00:05:37,110 --> 00:05:42,080
Shall we move forward with the marriage,
as a union between our families?

85
00:05:42,380 --> 00:05:46,680
First, I need to hear
what my Jun Ho thinks about it.

86
00:05:48,050 --> 00:05:51,790
He's never mentioned anything
about it at home.

87
00:05:52,560 --> 00:05:55,060
- Really?
- Thank you...

88
00:05:55,560 --> 00:05:58,260
for thinking so highly of him.

89
00:05:59,830 --> 00:06:00,830
Goodbye for now.

90
00:06:05,140 --> 00:06:06,570
I'll give you a call.

91
00:06:09,110 --> 00:06:12,340
So my Jun Ho is going to be the son-in-law
of Dream Group?

92
00:06:14,110 --> 00:06:17,280
But why hasn't Jun Ho said anything
about getting married?

93
00:06:17,750 --> 00:06:19,020
Not a single word.

94
00:06:20,950 --> 00:06:23,390
Minister, you saw the article?

95
00:06:25,360 --> 00:06:28,190
It's an annual poll.
Is it really that big of a deal?

96
00:06:28,390 --> 00:06:32,230
They say yesterday's poster girl
is now a Gen Z icon.

97
00:06:32,530 --> 00:06:33,530
Aren't you pleased?

98
00:06:33,800 --> 00:06:35,170
To be honest, I'm thrilled.

99
00:06:35,700 --> 00:06:39,000
I'm just trying not to
let it go to my head.

100
00:06:40,370 --> 00:06:44,080
A celebratory treat? Don't be silly.
Of course, I'll treat you.

101
00:06:44,480 --> 00:06:47,180
Yes, I'll be in touch, Minister.

102
00:06:47,710 --> 00:06:48,710
Okay.

103
00:07:03,190 --> 00:07:05,900
Hi, I'd like to order
a celebratory bouquet.

104
00:07:07,300 --> 00:07:09,930
One moment. I'll have to call you back.

105
00:07:12,470 --> 00:07:15,140
My mom's way too beautiful
not to have a boyfriend.

106
00:07:15,870 --> 00:07:18,310
But with her amnesia,
I can't just come out and ask her.

107
00:07:19,510 --> 00:07:24,120
Her boyfriend will likely get her flowers,
so maybe I should get her some jewelry?

108
00:07:25,120 --> 00:07:26,720
Team Leader Jin, you're here.

109
00:07:27,590 --> 00:07:29,590
I'm just running to the department store
for a bit.

110
00:07:31,190 --> 00:07:32,190
Okay.

111
00:07:39,730 --> 00:07:41,230
(Dream Project Office)

112
00:07:47,340 --> 00:07:49,710
A lover? Flowers?

113
00:07:56,950 --> 00:08:00,790
Mom, I just figured out
how we can really stick it to CEO Chae.

114
00:08:01,550 --> 00:08:03,320
Just as I predicted.

115
00:08:04,220 --> 00:08:08,490
Really? That's a great idea. Well, well.

116
00:08:08,830 --> 00:08:12,930
After all the times Chae Hwa Young
has slapped me around.

117
00:08:13,160 --> 00:08:16,730
Thinking of how horribly she treated me
makes my blood boil.

118
00:08:18,170 --> 00:08:21,710
With this move,
we can finally stick it to her.

119
00:08:22,770 --> 00:08:24,840
Hong Ju, you place the order. Got it?

120
00:08:25,110 --> 00:08:29,610
This is your chance to get her back
for some of what she's put you through.

121
00:08:34,150 --> 00:08:35,690
And while I'm at it,

122
00:08:36,120 --> 00:08:39,790
I'm going to tell the Chairman
everything he's done to upset me.

123
00:08:44,600 --> 00:08:45,600
Hello?

124
00:08:46,260 --> 00:08:48,000
I'd like to place an order
for flower delivery.

125
00:08:52,670 --> 00:08:54,810
With the increase in guests this season,

126
00:08:55,170 --> 00:08:58,040
we must diligently disinfect and sanitize
throughout the hotel.

127
00:08:58,440 --> 00:09:02,750
These are by no means minor issues,
so be clear with the departments involved.

128
00:09:02,810 --> 00:09:04,850
I've spoken with housekeeping,

129
00:09:05,150 --> 00:09:09,220
for high-touch spots like door handles,
remotes, and minibar handles,

130
00:09:09,350 --> 00:09:13,890
they'll disinfect them more thoroughly,
along with sanitizing the shower stalls.

131
00:09:14,360 --> 00:09:18,730
But when it comes to indoor cleanliness,
ventilation and purification are key,

132
00:09:19,100 --> 00:09:22,930
but we should also replace the filters
in the HVAC system more frequently.

133
00:09:23,130 --> 00:09:26,070
Director Ma, do you have a specific reason
for that suggestion?

134
00:09:26,340 --> 00:09:29,210
Guests are sensitive about air quality
these days.

135
00:09:29,640 --> 00:09:31,340
Our hotel goes the extra mile,
even in unseen areas.

136
00:09:31,410 --> 00:09:34,710
If we keep a disinfection log
showing our exceptional air management,

137
00:09:35,010 --> 00:09:36,610
we can leave guests...

138
00:09:36,680 --> 00:09:39,820
with an impression of cleanliness
that befits our reputation.

139
00:09:40,050 --> 00:09:42,450
All right, let's forward that
to the facilities team.

140
00:09:42,690 --> 00:09:47,330
Team Leader Jin, please make sure
to add this to our website announcements.

141
00:09:49,360 --> 00:09:50,460
As for you, Director Ma,

142
00:09:50,830 --> 00:09:52,600
it seems you're really getting the hang
of this job.

143
00:09:53,130 --> 00:09:54,430
You're improving every day.

144
00:09:55,300 --> 00:09:57,940
You just see more
when you're invested in it.

145
00:10:01,970 --> 00:10:04,280
Okay, what's on your mind?

146
00:10:04,910 --> 00:10:08,550
I'm ashamed to face Hong Ju, honey.

147
00:10:09,350 --> 00:10:10,550
What are you talking about?

148
00:10:11,350 --> 00:10:15,420
Hong Ju's last name is still Jin, not Ma.

149
00:10:15,850 --> 00:10:18,820
You only dote on Seo Rin
and want to give her everything,

150
00:10:19,320 --> 00:10:20,890
and we're just left out in the cold.

151
00:10:22,790 --> 00:10:24,300
It just makes me think...

152
00:10:25,030 --> 00:10:26,660
What am I even in this house?

153
00:10:27,030 --> 00:10:30,270
My life is just so pathetic
and miserable...

154
00:10:31,140 --> 00:10:32,240
That's enough.

155
00:10:32,940 --> 00:10:33,940
What?

156
00:10:34,910 --> 00:10:35,910
Mrs. Yeom.

157
00:10:36,170 --> 00:10:39,180
Don't you remember the desperate situation
you were in when I took you in?

158
00:10:40,440 --> 00:10:43,510
No, of course I remember.

159
00:10:43,580 --> 00:10:47,250
Back then, you said you'd be happy with me
just taking you and your daughter in.

160
00:10:47,620 --> 00:10:49,020
So why are you complaining more and more?

161
00:10:49,650 --> 00:10:51,560
Have you gotten greedy all of a sudden?

162
00:10:51,860 --> 00:10:52,920
Chairman.

163
00:10:53,690 --> 00:10:58,300
We may not have had a wedding,
but I still call you my husband...

164
00:10:59,130 --> 00:11:02,500
- You're being too harsh.
- Then don't call me your husband.

165
00:11:02,730 --> 00:11:05,170
What? No, no.

166
00:11:05,470 --> 00:11:08,470
- I will, honey.
- This all takes time.

167
00:11:08,570 --> 00:11:12,040
You and Hong Ju need time
to fit in with this family.

168
00:11:12,440 --> 00:11:14,810
If you're going to keep bothering me
by whining like this,

169
00:11:15,650 --> 00:11:16,710
you can go back to where you started.

170
00:11:16,780 --> 00:11:20,020
No. I'll never say anything
like that again.

171
00:11:20,650 --> 00:11:21,790
Chairman.

172
00:11:22,750 --> 00:11:26,460
I have enough stress and headaches
from work.

173
00:11:27,190 --> 00:11:29,690
Your job here at home, Mrs. Yeom,

174
00:11:30,190 --> 00:11:33,300
is to take care of me
so I don't have to worry about a thing.

175
00:11:33,600 --> 00:11:36,700
That's what the allowance
and credit card are for.

176
00:11:37,070 --> 00:11:38,200
What more do you need?

177
00:11:40,770 --> 00:11:41,870
You're right.

178
00:11:46,710 --> 00:11:49,410
Well, that backfired.
I tried to fix it and made it worse.

179
00:11:50,310 --> 00:11:54,020
That sly old fox is using a smokescreen
just to avoid giving me a dime.

180
00:11:54,850 --> 00:11:56,190
So where does that leave me?

181
00:11:56,550 --> 00:11:59,560
What am I doing,
slaving away for that old man for this?

182
00:12:01,230 --> 00:12:03,790
I can't believe it's this hard
just to get a few crumbs from the table.

183
00:12:07,130 --> 00:12:08,830
All right, Ma Dae Chang.

184
00:12:09,170 --> 00:12:12,570
Let's just see who wins this. You or me.

185
00:12:16,170 --> 00:12:20,080
No, hold on. A woman in my position,
as the lady of Dream Group,

186
00:12:20,140 --> 00:12:21,810
has to maintain her dignity.

187
00:12:22,610 --> 00:12:25,680
Bright red lipstick looks undignified,

188
00:12:27,150 --> 00:12:29,190
so I'll use this one instead.

189
00:12:31,590 --> 00:12:35,430
- Mrs. Yeom, aren't you ready yet?
- Oh my!

190
00:12:35,830 --> 00:12:37,190
Yes, I'm coming!

191
00:12:38,260 --> 00:12:40,800
Gosh, so now he's offering a carrot?

192
00:12:41,570 --> 00:12:43,130
He's an expert at playing hot and cold.

193
00:12:54,510 --> 00:12:55,610
Geum Soon.

194
00:12:57,580 --> 00:13:00,920
My husband and I are going out.
Look after the house while we're gone.

195
00:13:02,690 --> 00:13:04,390
Have a good time, Chairman.

196
00:13:06,760 --> 00:13:10,160
You've got to be kidding me, Geum Soon.
Why aren't you saying goodbye to me?

197
00:13:11,200 --> 00:13:12,930
It's like you're treating me
like I'm invisible.

198
00:13:25,680 --> 00:13:27,040
Did you forget something?

199
00:13:30,150 --> 00:13:32,180
Oh my gosh, honey.

200
00:13:32,580 --> 00:13:34,990
Why haven't you been answering my calls?

201
00:13:35,720 --> 00:13:36,750
You little...

202
00:13:38,460 --> 00:13:40,320
Darn it.

203
00:13:46,430 --> 00:13:48,170
Seriously.

204
00:13:49,630 --> 00:13:53,540
Hey! There's a limit to how much
you can disrespect your husband!

205
00:13:54,240 --> 00:13:55,610
You think if you avoid me,

206
00:13:55,910 --> 00:13:57,710
that I wouldn't find you?
Is that why you're blowing me off?

207
00:13:58,510 --> 00:14:01,310
I'm sorry, stop. I'll never do it again.

208
00:14:01,380 --> 00:14:03,280
You're all talk.

209
00:14:06,250 --> 00:14:08,450
- Gosh!
- Seo Rin?

210
00:14:08,520 --> 00:14:10,290
Hey, who the heck are you?

211
00:14:10,820 --> 00:14:12,820
Did you just hit the back of my head
with that thing?

212
00:14:13,590 --> 00:14:14,590
Yes.

213
00:14:15,860 --> 00:14:19,200
I'm the granddaughter here. So?
Heard of Chairman Ma from Dream Group?

214
00:14:19,500 --> 00:14:23,270
I'm his one and only blood relative.
You just lay one finger on me.

215
00:14:23,570 --> 00:14:27,000
The second you do, I'll have you arrested,
and you won't be getting out.

216
00:14:27,140 --> 00:14:28,140
Got it?

217
00:14:28,540 --> 00:14:29,570
Unbelievable. Darn it.

218
00:14:30,170 --> 00:14:31,580
Ma'am, are you okay?

219
00:14:31,840 --> 00:14:33,080
You're sure you don't
need to go to a hospital?

220
00:14:33,680 --> 00:14:35,250
I'm fine, but...

221
00:14:37,880 --> 00:14:39,580
What do you think you're doing?

222
00:14:39,850 --> 00:14:41,520
I'm getting proof. Why?

223
00:14:41,790 --> 00:14:44,520
Proof that you trespassed
and assaulted your wife.

224
00:14:44,720 --> 00:14:46,660
Darn it, this is ridiculous.

225
00:14:47,690 --> 00:14:51,830
Hey! I'm leaving, but you just wait.
Run from me again and you'll be sorry.

226
00:14:52,860 --> 00:14:55,430
Where do you think you're going?
You came in whenever you wanted,

227
00:14:55,500 --> 00:14:58,570
- but you're not leaving when you want.
- What did you just say?

228
00:14:58,840 --> 00:14:59,840
Why you little...

229
00:15:03,270 --> 00:15:05,940
I saw the assault the moment
I walked in and called the police.

230
00:15:06,440 --> 00:15:09,010
What are you going to do?
To avoid hard time, get on your knees...

231
00:15:09,080 --> 00:15:13,380
and apologize. Then write a statement
promising you'll never hurt her again.

232
00:15:14,020 --> 00:15:16,290
Then I'll tell the police
it was a false alarm,

233
00:15:16,650 --> 00:15:17,660
and let you walk.

234
00:15:18,990 --> 00:15:21,160
You little brat.

235
00:15:21,660 --> 00:15:23,290
So? I'm running out of time.

236
00:15:32,570 --> 00:15:33,570
Jang Mi.

237
00:15:34,370 --> 00:15:36,740
You know I can wait forever for you...

238
00:15:37,840 --> 00:15:38,840
But still...

239
00:15:39,380 --> 00:15:40,980
couldn't you please wake up
a little sooner?

240
00:15:46,120 --> 00:15:47,890
Baek Ho! You're here.

241
00:15:48,150 --> 00:15:51,320
- You're here.
- Tok Hee is asleep.

242
00:15:51,720 --> 00:15:53,190
Tok Hee's been sleeping for a long time.

243
00:15:54,020 --> 00:15:58,300
- Tok Hee is asleep.
- She'll wake up soon, don't you worry.

244
00:15:59,160 --> 00:16:00,500
Who knows when that'll be.

245
00:16:01,030 --> 00:16:02,670
Even the strongest person
gets worn out by a long illness.

246
00:16:03,300 --> 00:16:05,340
I'm getting exhausted too, Jang Mi.

247
00:16:05,600 --> 00:16:08,270
Mom, Tok Hee is your doll.
What's with all this "Tok Hee" talk?

248
00:16:08,810 --> 00:16:09,810
Mom.

249
00:16:10,810 --> 00:16:14,380
Tok Hee needs to eat too.
Hurry up and wake up.

250
00:16:14,880 --> 00:16:18,180
Jang Mi is so pretty. I miss Jang Mi.

251
00:16:19,220 --> 00:16:21,790
I want to see her wake up too.

252
00:16:24,290 --> 00:16:25,590
Jang Mi, please wake up soon.

253
00:16:26,990 --> 00:16:29,260
By the way, have you heard from CEO Chae?

254
00:16:29,560 --> 00:16:31,460
What nerve would she have to contact us?

255
00:16:32,500 --> 00:16:33,630
What's that supposed to mean?

256
00:16:34,670 --> 00:16:36,030
It's nothing, just...

257
00:16:37,230 --> 00:16:38,570
Stop fooling around and let's go.

258
00:16:38,840 --> 00:16:41,540
We don't have time to be chit-chatting
if we have to pack a hundred lunch boxes.

259
00:16:41,770 --> 00:16:44,940
- A hundred lunch boxes?
- Yes, that's the order we got.

260
00:16:46,040 --> 00:16:49,410
- That's huge. Are you sure it's legit?
- We were already paid in advance.

261
00:16:49,750 --> 00:16:52,020
- For Tok Hee.
- It's Tok Hee.

262
00:16:52,820 --> 00:16:54,450
Tok Hee is hurting.

263
00:17:03,790 --> 00:17:04,800
Honey.

264
00:17:05,060 --> 00:17:07,770
At this rate,
our Hong Ju is going to collapse.

265
00:17:08,170 --> 00:17:09,770
She does nothing but work, day and night.

266
00:17:09,830 --> 00:17:13,570
At that rate, every office worker in Korea
would have collapsed by now.

267
00:17:17,140 --> 00:17:21,910
You should delegate some of the work.
Seo Rin is back on the job now.

268
00:17:24,080 --> 00:17:25,080
Yes.

269
00:17:31,420 --> 00:17:34,630
Oh my, what are the flowers for?
Are those for me?

270
00:17:34,830 --> 00:17:37,830
This came for you, ma'am.
I picked it up out front.

271
00:17:38,730 --> 00:17:42,130
- For me?
- Oh my, a bouquet for Mom?

272
00:17:44,500 --> 00:17:46,700
Looks like the former star's still got it.

273
00:17:46,770 --> 00:17:50,640
Back in her heyday, men were always
sending your mom flowers.

274
00:17:50,770 --> 00:17:51,780
Men, you say?

275
00:17:52,210 --> 00:17:54,750
Then I bet this bouquet
is from a boyfriend, right?

276
00:17:54,880 --> 00:17:58,350
A boyfriend? Don't be ridiculous.
I don't have one of those.

277
00:17:59,880 --> 00:18:01,650
(Kang Nam Bong)

278
00:18:01,950 --> 00:18:03,290
"Kang Nam Bong?"

279
00:18:03,650 --> 00:18:05,920
Oh my. If that's Kang Nam Bong...

280
00:18:06,590 --> 00:18:08,160
You mean Professor Kang?

281
00:18:08,460 --> 00:18:11,530
- I think so, Mom.
- Who's Professor Kang Nam Bong?

282
00:18:12,400 --> 00:18:15,700
- Is he really your boyfriend?
- You mean that Professor Kang?

283
00:18:15,930 --> 00:18:18,140
Honey, it's that professor, you know?

284
00:18:19,370 --> 00:18:22,670
- It's him, right?
- Yes, the one people were talking about.

285
00:18:23,510 --> 00:18:25,840
But why would Professor Kang Nam Bong...

286
00:18:26,210 --> 00:18:28,550
send you a bouquet of flowers?

287
00:18:30,280 --> 00:18:32,020
What does the card say, Seo Rin?

288
00:18:32,450 --> 00:18:35,990
What's going on?
Am I the only one who doesn't know?

289
00:18:36,590 --> 00:18:38,560
Fill me in.

290
00:18:38,860 --> 00:18:40,990
Boyfriend? Watch your mouth.

291
00:18:41,660 --> 00:18:43,930
He's just a colleague
I worked on a project with.

292
00:18:44,760 --> 00:18:45,760
Really?

293
00:18:47,330 --> 00:18:49,930
He must have heard I was named
one of the top three female CEOs.

294
00:18:50,700 --> 00:18:52,870
So he must've sent them
to congratulate me.

295
00:18:53,940 --> 00:18:56,870
That's how it starts.
First colleagues, then something more.

296
00:18:56,940 --> 00:18:59,240
You're single, Mom.
What's wrong with dating?

297
00:18:59,510 --> 00:19:03,280
- I'm all for you dating, Mom.
- There are right and wrong ways to date.

298
00:19:03,710 --> 00:19:05,150
But wouldn't an affair
with a married man...

299
00:19:05,450 --> 00:19:07,680
be a problem for the company?

300
00:19:07,780 --> 00:19:10,890
- What? An affair?
- That's right.

301
00:19:11,160 --> 00:19:14,660
That man is married and has a family.

302
00:19:17,530 --> 00:19:20,630
She's right. If the CEO
dates a married man,

303
00:19:21,600 --> 00:19:23,930
- it'll blow up.
- Will you all just stop it?

304
00:19:25,940 --> 00:19:30,140
Father, I'm being wrongly accused.
As I have told you before,

305
00:19:30,510 --> 00:19:34,910
Professor Kang and I are just colleagues.
Nothing more, nothing less.

306
00:19:35,180 --> 00:19:38,820
Watch how you act so no strange rumors
start spreading around the company.

307
00:19:39,250 --> 00:19:43,020
You of all people know how much
money is riding on you...

308
00:19:43,220 --> 00:19:44,490
at our company, Dream.

309
00:19:45,360 --> 00:19:46,390
I won't say this again.

310
00:19:59,870 --> 00:20:03,510
Did you see that? The way Chae Hwa Young
was squirming with a sour look.

311
00:20:04,640 --> 00:20:05,640
So satisfying.

312
00:20:05,840 --> 00:20:10,750
I've never seen the CEO look so flustered.
I feel like I'm finally getting payback.

313
00:20:11,050 --> 00:20:13,180
I'm loving this.

314
00:20:18,620 --> 00:20:20,520
Looks like someone did
my dirty work for me.

315
00:20:21,860 --> 00:20:23,030
Chae Hwa Young,

316
00:20:23,490 --> 00:20:25,330
you have to pay the price
for having an affair.

317
00:20:34,470 --> 00:20:37,610
What do you mean,
asking if the CEO said anything?

318
00:20:37,940 --> 00:20:41,680
Your CEO is thinking of you
as a potential son-in-law.

319
00:20:42,650 --> 00:20:43,650
What?

320
00:20:44,180 --> 00:20:47,850
So, you're saying CEO Chae Hwa Young
wants our Jun Ho to be her son-in-law?

321
00:20:48,020 --> 00:20:50,720
She was just making conversation.
You don't have to take it seriously.

322
00:20:50,820 --> 00:20:53,260
That's not something
you just say casually.

323
00:20:53,520 --> 00:20:55,490
Why would CEO Chae want you
as a son-in-law?

324
00:20:56,030 --> 00:20:57,390
After all the grief she gives you?

325
00:20:57,490 --> 00:20:59,560
Anyway, with what happened
with your dad and all,

326
00:20:59,660 --> 00:21:02,570
the CEO said she'd be in touch
within a few days.

327
00:21:02,900 --> 00:21:05,800
Honey, stop it. It was bad enough
that you went begging,

328
00:21:05,870 --> 00:21:07,970
but now you're trying
to sell your own son?

329
00:21:08,470 --> 00:21:10,410
What are you talking about,
selling my son?

330
00:21:10,670 --> 00:21:15,080
CEO Chae told me
she said we should become in-laws!

331
00:21:15,150 --> 00:21:16,610
Gosh, that's ridiculous.

332
00:21:16,710 --> 00:21:18,750
And what's so ridiculous about it?

333
00:21:19,850 --> 00:21:23,490
Is there some law that says
our Jun Ho can't marry an heiress?

334
00:21:23,590 --> 00:21:27,190
- That marriage is out of the question.
- No, something feels off.

335
00:21:27,720 --> 00:21:30,530
So you're actually waiting for a call
from CEO Chae, Mom?

336
00:21:34,900 --> 00:21:38,540
Sending flowers to my house?
What are you up to, Professor Kang?

337
00:21:39,340 --> 00:21:43,210
Your dad's car accident
was because of work,

338
00:21:43,270 --> 00:21:46,310
so I gave them a piece of my mind,
telling them to take responsibility.

339
00:21:46,580 --> 00:21:48,510
She didn't say anything to me about it.

340
00:21:51,210 --> 00:21:52,220
Oh my.

341
00:21:52,380 --> 00:21:55,750
CEO Chae didn't call me.
She's calling you directly.

342
00:21:56,150 --> 00:21:57,150
Quick, answer it.

343
00:22:02,530 --> 00:22:03,530
Pick up.

344
00:22:04,090 --> 00:22:05,600
Pick up the phone.

345
00:22:11,840 --> 00:22:13,240
Hello, this is Kang Nam Bong.

346
00:22:13,370 --> 00:22:16,440
Professor, what in the world
do you think you're doing?

347
00:22:16,710 --> 00:22:20,140
Sending flowers to my house?
Wasn't that incredibly reckless of you?

348
00:22:20,710 --> 00:22:23,350
Excuse me?
What on earth are you talking about?

349
00:22:24,950 --> 00:22:26,050
Hold on.

350
00:22:34,930 --> 00:22:36,160
What flowers?

351
00:22:36,460 --> 00:22:41,030
My entire family is here.
Do you think I'm crazy enough to do that?

352
00:22:42,400 --> 00:22:44,270
You really didn't send them, Professor?

353
00:22:44,600 --> 00:22:47,100
Of course not. It wasn't me.

354
00:22:48,510 --> 00:22:49,740
Then who?

355
00:22:51,640 --> 00:22:52,640
I'm so sorry.

356
00:22:53,510 --> 00:22:56,110
A bouquet arrived at my house
with your name on it.

357
00:22:56,610 --> 00:22:58,120
So I had no choice.

358
00:22:58,380 --> 00:23:01,080
I told them you heard
I was named a top female CEO,

359
00:23:01,250 --> 00:23:04,790
and you sent the flowers
to congratulate me.

360
00:23:05,820 --> 00:23:08,430
- Just play along.
- Okay, got it.

361
00:23:08,630 --> 00:23:10,860
I'll call you back later, then.

362
00:23:14,330 --> 00:23:17,700
This came for you, ma'am.
I picked it up out front.

363
00:23:20,500 --> 00:23:22,610
Jin Hong Ju. It was you again, wasn't it?

364
00:23:23,640 --> 00:23:27,340
This is the same trick you pulled
with the note at the office.

365
00:23:27,940 --> 00:23:32,280
Jin Hong Ju, how am I going to
make you pay for this?

366
00:23:33,450 --> 00:23:35,990
Do you really think
you'll get away with this?

367
00:23:37,620 --> 00:23:41,190
I'll expose all your dirty secrets,
one by one.

368
00:23:41,760 --> 00:23:43,330
Just you wait, Chae Hwa Young.

369
00:23:51,900 --> 00:23:53,240
What did CEO Chae say?

370
00:23:54,300 --> 00:23:55,810
It's nothing.

371
00:23:56,170 --> 00:24:00,510
I heard that CEO Chae was named
one of the top three female CEOs,

372
00:24:01,110 --> 00:24:03,650
so I had some flowers sent
to congratulate her.

373
00:24:04,780 --> 00:24:09,050
- She was just calling to say thank you.
- Wow, I didn't know you had that in you.

374
00:24:09,120 --> 00:24:10,820
Oh my, Dad, I didn't know
you did stuff like that.

375
00:24:15,160 --> 00:24:16,560
Invite who?

376
00:24:16,990 --> 00:24:18,230
Professor Kang Nam Bong.

377
00:24:18,730 --> 00:24:23,030
He sent Mom a bouquet.
It wouldn't be right to just ignore it.

378
00:24:23,530 --> 00:24:26,470
- And...
- Is he having an affair with your mom?

379
00:24:27,040 --> 00:24:28,540
So that's what
you're really curious about.

380
00:24:29,940 --> 00:24:33,540
If Mom is having an affair like you said,
we'll be in big trouble.

381
00:24:33,910 --> 00:24:35,610
After all the hard work
you put into building this company,

382
00:24:36,080 --> 00:24:38,280
we can't just let it all
fall apart overnight.

383
00:24:39,820 --> 00:24:43,720
It's so sweet of you to be thinking
of your old grandpa, Seo Rin.

384
00:24:45,090 --> 00:24:49,060
But I want it to look like
you're the one inviting him, Grandfather.

385
00:24:49,160 --> 00:24:53,530
Of course. All right.
Let's make it happen.

386
00:24:54,000 --> 00:24:55,330
Thank you, Grandfather.

387
00:24:58,400 --> 00:25:01,340
(Suk Hee's Side Dishes)

388
00:25:12,150 --> 00:25:14,950
Oh my, a standing order
for 100 sets a week?

389
00:25:14,950 --> 00:25:16,350
This is great, Tae Pyung.

390
00:25:16,450 --> 00:25:17,520
Right?

391
00:25:18,090 --> 00:25:19,160
It sure is.

392
00:25:19,720 --> 00:25:20,820
Anyway,

393
00:25:21,190 --> 00:25:25,130
now that Bo Ra and I live on our own,
I need to become financially independent.

394
00:25:25,400 --> 00:25:29,700
- Hey, what are you getting at now?
- You know the shabu-shabu where I work?

395
00:25:29,830 --> 00:25:33,000
The manager asked if I was interested
in taking over the restaurant.

396
00:25:33,070 --> 00:25:35,240
What? You want to run your own business?

397
00:25:35,310 --> 00:25:37,010
It's in a prime location
with a lot of customers.

398
00:25:37,070 --> 00:25:40,210
And the ingredients from corporate
are always fresh and high-quality.

399
00:25:40,380 --> 00:25:42,410
Why would I ever pass up
an offer like that?

400
00:25:42,550 --> 00:25:46,620
Now, now, look before you leap.
Do your homework before you start one.

401
00:25:46,880 --> 00:25:48,850
If you do sign a contract,
let me come with you.

402
00:25:49,350 --> 00:25:52,790
Baek Ho, that would be so reassuring.
Thank you so much.

403
00:25:53,120 --> 00:25:55,590
Besides, they said they offer
thorough business consulting.

404
00:25:56,260 --> 00:26:01,060
Tae Pyung, don't worry.
I'll be able to pay you back monthly.

405
00:26:01,260 --> 00:26:02,500
Gosh, for crying out loud.

406
00:26:03,870 --> 00:26:04,940
Good grief.

407
00:26:09,110 --> 00:26:10,110
Yes?

408
00:26:16,550 --> 00:26:20,220
This is freshly squeezed. Drink up.
Since you don't eat breakfast,

409
00:26:20,650 --> 00:26:22,420
the CEO asked me to bring it to you.

410
00:26:22,850 --> 00:26:25,020
Okay, thank you.

411
00:26:26,160 --> 00:26:29,490
I'm sorry! Oh no!

412
00:26:35,270 --> 00:26:36,470
You're not Seo Rin, are you?

413
00:26:37,370 --> 00:26:39,940
What? Ma'am, what are you talking about?

414
00:26:40,040 --> 00:26:43,370
I've been watching you,
and a lot of things don't add up.

415
00:26:44,110 --> 00:26:47,880
Since when have you ever made your bed?
Now it's always neatly folded.

416
00:26:47,940 --> 00:26:50,410
You used to hate sweet rice punch,
but now you're always asking for it.

417
00:26:50,480 --> 00:26:52,720
And you won't even eat the fish eyeballs
you used to love so much.

418
00:26:52,850 --> 00:26:54,620
And on top of all that,
you're cleaning the floor?

419
00:26:55,020 --> 00:26:58,250
You're not the type to do these things.
I know you.

420
00:26:58,320 --> 00:27:01,160
Stop it! Just be quiet, please!

421
00:27:01,220 --> 00:27:05,130
- I'm right, aren't I? You're not Seo Rin.
- Stop! Ma'am...

422
00:27:05,530 --> 00:27:06,530
Seo Rin.

423
00:27:10,300 --> 00:27:12,770
Why are you covering her mouth like that?

424
00:27:13,370 --> 00:27:15,570
- What on earth is going on?
- What?

425
00:27:17,340 --> 00:27:18,480
Ma'am, tell me.

426
00:27:19,080 --> 00:27:21,980
Why was Seo Rin just covering your mouth?

427
00:27:50,970 --> 00:27:52,480
(The First Man)

428
00:27:52,540 --> 00:27:56,480
If things go well,
I might even marry Lawyer Kang this year.

429
00:27:56,680 --> 00:27:58,210
What? Get married?

430
00:27:58,480 --> 00:28:02,520
- Is that true?
- She hit Seo Rin and me with a truck.

431
00:28:02,590 --> 00:28:06,660
- How could a human being do such a thing?
- I'm going to make Chae Hwa Young pay.

432
00:28:06,920 --> 00:28:09,360
I heard someone died in the car accident.

433
00:28:09,830 --> 00:28:13,000
But Professor,
what were you doing there at that hour?

434
00:28:14,560 --> 00:28:16,570
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
